title: Nosy Whale
text:
My name is Emma. I am a biologist in my honours year at the University of Cape Town.
I am interested in marine megafauna. Itâ€™s easy to realise our insignificance when facing a gentle giant. I am curious about whale and shark behaviour, communication, distribution, and genetics. I am interested in how climate change is altering nature and how nature is evolving in spite of it. I am interested in humans and how they interact with the world around them.
